WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

01:46.981 --> 01:48.774
(Phone rings)

01:52.028 --> 01:53.195
Yeah.

01:53.321 --> 01:54.488
Oh.

01:54.614 --> 01:56.323
Oh, Jesus, no.

01:56.449 --> 01:57.950
This isn't a good time.

02:00.036 --> 02:01.703
(Sheriff) Rick?

02:03.039 --> 02:05.457
- Mr Carver?
- Yeah, I'll be with you in a second.

02:06.709 --> 02:08.460
Huh? Well, I'll tell you what you do.

02:08.586 --> 02:12.172
Remove the meter, turn the water off,
and let them sweat for a couple of days.

02:12.298 --> 02:14.216
Then you ride in
on your white fucking horse,

02:14.342 --> 02:16.093
tell them you have a cash buyer

02:16.219 --> 02:18.470
and Richard Carver
can approve a short sale.

02:18.596 --> 02:21.098
You want me to spell it for you?
R-I-C...

02:21.224 --> 02:24.643
OK, well, I can't hold your hand
while you give them a hand job, Bill.

02:24.769 --> 02:26.645
Just get me the property.

02:27.480 --> 02:31.316
Yes, John, Officer Dudura, you have
my court order signed by the judge.

02:31.442 --> 02:33.068
What can I do for you?

02:33.194 --> 02:35.237
You're the bank's realtor
on this eviction.

02:35.363 --> 02:38.699
I need an official statement.
What happened and why?

02:38.825 --> 02:41.743
Well, Dudura, it's a real shame
cos we arrived here with two pizzas

02:41.870 --> 02:44.163
for Mr Kadwell, the property owner,

02:44.289 --> 02:46.165
but he didn't want anchovies,

02:46.291 --> 02:48.750
so he went into the house,
pulled out a gun

02:48.877 --> 02:51.044
and he blew his brains out.

02:51.171 --> 02:54.506
And that set off Mrs Kadwell
who was expecting Chinese for dinner.

02:55.592 --> 02:58.093
You're talking about a man
who just killed himself.

03:01.764 --> 03:05.017
I am the last man who knocked
on Patrick Kadwell's door,

03:05.143 --> 03:06.643
in his life.

03:06.769 --> 03:08.979
That is his wife of 15 years, Samantha,

03:09.105 --> 03:11.648
his daughters,
Dylan, six, Paige, 11.

03:12.734 --> 03:14.568
What official statement
can encapsulate

03:14.694 --> 03:17.487
the tragic absurdity
of this fucked-up situation?

03:17.614 --> 03:20.407
I can't bring him back to life.
Stop wasting my time.

03:20.533 --> 03:22.868
(Phone rings)

03:22.994 --> 03:24.036
Yeah?

03:24.162 --> 03:25.621
No, I'm fine, honey.

03:25.747 --> 03:28.832
Turn the TV off,
keep the girls away from the internet.

03:28.958 --> 03:30.042
Er...

03:30.168 --> 03:32.044
I got a call. Yeah.

03:32.837 --> 03:33.921
Hello?

03:34.672 --> 03:36.632
No, no, no.
You ride that up to 200.

03:37.467 --> 03:39.468
220 tops.
No more than 10% down.

03:39.594 --> 03:42.179
7.5% makes me sing.
Get the Miguels ready.

03:42.305 --> 03:44.097
It's two grand a month
in interest alone.

03:44.224 --> 03:46.183
We got to flip this thing.
Get back to me.

03:46.309 --> 03:48.268
(Beep)

03:48.394 --> 03:50.938
- Call office.
- (Dialling tone)

03:51.064 --> 03:53.523
Have we got anything else, boss?

03:53.650 --> 03:56.401
Next eviction's Tuesday.
Natalia will call you.

03:56.527 --> 03:57.736
Roger that.

04:01.407 --> 04:04.451
- (Natalia) 'Rick Carver Realty.'
- Talk to me. My world's upside down.

04:04.577 --> 04:07.537
'I'm emailing your revised itinerary.
And Jerry called again...'

04:07.664 --> 04:09.498
Jerry's full of shit.
Keep talking.

04:09.624 --> 04:12.501
'The Sutton Place high-rise came up.
The UD's in order.

04:13.461 --> 04:15.254
'What do you want me to tell Elliot?'

04:15.380 --> 04:18.257
(Samantha) No, no!

04:23.972 --> 04:25.264
Please!

04:47.370 --> 04:50.455
Yo, Nash, you can stop working now.
We're done. We're done.

04:50.581 --> 04:51.999
- What?
- Hey!

04:53.126 --> 04:55.002
Listen up!

04:55.128 --> 04:56.586
(Speaks Spanish)

04:57.755 --> 04:59.965
The buyer didn't qualify.
We're shut down.

05:00.091 --> 05:02.217
- What about payment?
- We don't get paid.

05:02.343 --> 05:04.177
For two weeks
we've been working for free.

05:04.304 --> 05:07.264
All this from roof to cement
is for nothing.

05:07.390 --> 05:09.182
- Stop working!
- (Hammering)

05:09.309 --> 05:10.809
Put the hammer down, man.

05:10.935 --> 05:13.562
Unplug everything, wrap it up.
Let's go home.

05:13.688 --> 05:14.980
No dinero.

05:15.106 --> 05:18.692
That looks like the United States
upside down, but flipped this way.

05:18.818 --> 05:21.570
- It actually does.
- (Dennis) Connor?

05:21.696 --> 05:22.904
Connor!

05:23.573 --> 05:25.699
- We were just looking at the countries.
- Connor!

05:25.825 --> 05:28.702
- We're naming the countries.
- It's our time. We're up.

05:28.828 --> 05:30.454
- Gotta go.
- See you.

05:30.580 --> 05:31.788
Bye.

05:32.915 --> 05:34.708
Who was that?

05:34.834 --> 05:37.044
- Who was that?
- That's my friend Alex from school.

05:38.504 --> 05:41.340
- You dropped this.
- Good catch.

05:41.466 --> 05:45.010
Your Honour, he missed three payments
and is underwater over 80 grand.

05:45.136 --> 05:47.721
The bank can have a buyer in place
within 30 days.

05:47.847 --> 05:51.058
- Did you in fact miss three payments?
- Yes, sir, but I was told to.

05:51.184 --> 05:54.436
Two departments at the same bank
were telling me opposing things

05:54.562 --> 05:57.647
and then, just recently,
I got a final notice for eviction.

05:57.774 --> 06:00.567
(Lawyer) We'd like to get
this property off the market.

06:00.693 --> 06:03.779
- I see no reason to hold up the sale.
- They told me not to pay.

06:03.905 --> 06:07.491
And that's why I'm behind.
They told me not to pay.

06:07.617 --> 06:11.328
While I sympathise with your situation
I have 40,000 cases like this

06:11.454 --> 06:12.913
backed up behind yours.

06:13.623 --> 06:16.541
Final judgment granted.
I'm ordering you to vacate the premises.

06:16.667 --> 06:20.170
That's my family home, Your Honour.
I was born and raised in that home.

06:21.547 --> 06:23.924
He was born and raised there too.
He's my son, Connor.

06:24.050 --> 06:26.510
Please don't do this.
We've lived there our whole lives.

06:26.636 --> 06:29.137
My mum runs her business
out of that home.

06:29.263 --> 06:31.348
That's our second source
of income right now.

06:31.474 --> 06:32.974
- Is this your son?
- That's my son.

06:33.101 --> 06:34.684
He should be in school and not here.

06:34.811 --> 06:36.937
He's gonna lose his school,
with all due respect.

06:37.063 --> 06:40.190
Sun United Bank versus R. Rogers.

06:43.361 --> 06:45.904
- Give me a bit more time, please.
- Please remove Mr Nash.

06:46.030 --> 06:48.448
Your Honour, I just need a bit more time.

06:48.574 --> 06:51.118
I need a bit more time.
Excuse me for a second.

06:51.244 --> 06:53.036
(Bailiff) I need you to follow me now.

06:53.162 --> 06:55.747
(Judge) You have 30 days
to file an appeal.

06:55.873 --> 06:58.834
- Bailiff, please remove Mr Nash.
- I need you to follow me now, sir.

06:58.960 --> 07:00.419
Right now.

07:10.471 --> 07:12.722
Where are we going to stay
if we lose our home?

07:15.852 --> 07:18.353
- We're not gonna lose the home, bud.
- How do you know?

07:19.689 --> 07:21.148
The cops are coming back.

07:21.774 --> 07:23.733
I just wanna know
how you're gonna pay for it.

07:23.860 --> 07:25.110
Connor.

07:28.322 --> 07:31.450
Connor, I'm gonna figure it out, OK?

07:31.576 --> 07:34.661
That judge gave us 30 days.
Ain't no one taking the home from us.

07:34.787 --> 07:37.706
I'm gonna win this.
I'm gonna figure it out, simple as that.

07:37.832 --> 07:38.915
We're good.

07:55.266 --> 07:56.308
(Dennis) One hour.

07:59.145 --> 08:01.188
Hey, Bo.

08:01.314 --> 08:04.691
I got that new blade for your skill saw.
I'll bring it over tonight.

08:04.817 --> 08:06.610
- OK.
- You be careful, Connor.

08:06.736 --> 08:08.862
- Got a new scooter?
- Yeah.

08:08.988 --> 08:11.531
(Dennis) Hey, Mum.
(Lynn) So, tell me everything.

08:11.657 --> 08:15.702
- Did they give you a lawyer?
- Mum, it's the same story.

08:15.828 --> 08:18.830
Same story with the bank guys.
It's the same story everywhere we go.

08:18.956 --> 08:20.457
We have to find a lawyer.

08:20.583 --> 08:23.627
I'm just trying to understand
what this 30-day thing means.

08:23.753 --> 08:26.588
Does that mean the eviction's
not gonna happen tomorrow?

08:26.714 --> 08:30.425
- The judge told you. It's 30 days.
- 30 days to file for an appeal.

08:30.551 --> 08:34.304
It's a judge, it's not a bartender.
We're in good shape.

08:34.429 --> 08:37.807
My name is Dennis Nash
and I'm looking for representation.

08:37.933 --> 08:41.144
I understand that you guys
sometimes do not need a retainer.

08:43.648 --> 08:45.982
When you went through
what you went through,

08:46.108 --> 08:49.069
you found someone pro bono.
I'm wondering if he's gonna help...

08:49.195 --> 08:53.782
Lost is to found
as outside is to indoors, inside...

08:53.908 --> 08:56.701
And what's another example?
Here you go.

08:56.827 --> 08:58.495
- Have some salad.
- Black and white.

08:58.621 --> 09:00.413
Black and white.

09:00.540 --> 09:02.165
What's another one?
Give me one more.

09:02.708 --> 09:06.962
4540189.
Please give us a call back.

09:15.680 --> 09:17.764
I don't know
what to say to him sometimes.

09:17.890 --> 09:20.100
I was so young when I had you.

09:22.186 --> 09:23.895
I feel like you've had to raise me.

09:28.693 --> 09:30.360
You know just what to say.

09:42.623 --> 09:45.750
(lndistinct chat)

09:46.877 --> 09:49.421
Borrow against Blair Street
to cover Via Alizar.

09:49.547 --> 09:50.755
(Natalia) 'Good.'

09:50.881 --> 09:54.092
- I'll flip that this quarter.
- 'And London at Code Enforcement?'

09:54.802 --> 09:58.638
I got a short sale for that cocksucker.
I'll email you the details.

09:58.764 --> 10:00.223
- 'OK.'
- All right.

10:00.349 --> 10:04.019
(Sheriff) Afternoon, boss.
Love the new ride.

10:04.145 --> 10:07.897
- Range Rover HSE.
- Is this the Nash eviction?

10:08.899 --> 10:10.275
Yeah. Anyone home?

10:10.401 --> 10:14.613
I'm not sure, but his vehicle is home,
so I'm assuming he is.

10:16.782 --> 10:18.867
All right, let's get to it.

10:21.203 --> 10:23.079
- Morning, y'all.
- How's it going?

10:39.639 --> 10:41.348
(Sheriff) He's at the window.

10:42.767 --> 10:43.808
(Banging on door)

10:43.934 --> 10:46.227
Sheriff's department.
Come to the door.

10:56.822 --> 10:58.323
- What?
- Sheriffs are here.

10:58.449 --> 11:00.408
(Banging on door)

11:01.494 --> 11:03.161
Why are they here?

11:04.372 --> 11:06.665
(Banging on door)

11:06.791 --> 11:08.708
- You need to come to the door.
- He saw you.

11:08.834 --> 11:12.379
They saw you through the window.
Just answer it. We just got to explain it.

11:12.505 --> 11:14.381
Oh, come on.
Don't fucking do this.

11:14.507 --> 11:15.965
(Banging at door)

11:17.885 --> 11:19.344
- Good afternoon.
- Afternoon.

11:19.470 --> 11:21.971
I'm Deputy Anderson
with the Sheriff's department.

11:22.098 --> 11:24.307
We're here to serve you
a court-ordered eviction.

11:24.433 --> 11:26.309
- OK, well...
- So, ma'am,

11:26.435 --> 11:29.521
do you have any weapons on your body
or anywhere in the house?

11:29.647 --> 11:32.440
- No, no, no, no. Not us.
- Mr Carver?

11:32.566 --> 11:34.442
Good morning.
My name's Rick Carver.

11:34.568 --> 11:37.070
- I'm a licensed real estate broker.
- (Dennis) Mr Carver.

11:37.196 --> 11:38.238
Hi. Lynn.

11:38.364 --> 11:40.573
And, er, I'm very sorry to tell you

11:40.700 --> 11:44.411
that this home has been foreclosed on
and officially transferred to the bank.

11:44.537 --> 11:48.456
- I need you to vacate the premises.
- I understand what you're saying.

11:48.582 --> 11:49.916
And I've... I've... I've...

11:50.042 --> 11:51.876
We've been getting
our eviction notices.

11:52.002 --> 11:54.003
I was in court yesterday

11:54.130 --> 11:57.298
and the judge informed me
that I got 30 days

11:57.425 --> 11:59.843
to file for an appeal
and that's what I intend to do.

11:59.969 --> 12:03.930
If you have an emergency stay signed
by the judge, you're welcome to remain.

12:04.056 --> 12:07.642
I got a question. You guys didn't get
any rescheduling of the eviction date?

12:07.768 --> 12:10.270
What I've received is a court order
signed by a judge.

12:10.396 --> 12:13.189
It says you are to vacate
these premises today.

12:13.315 --> 12:16.067
- We were scared of this.
- This home is owned by the bank.

12:16.193 --> 12:20.155
- This is the information that we have.
- And we're sorry to waste your time.

12:20.281 --> 12:24.367
My office offered you a $3500
cash-or-keys settlement from the bank

12:24.493 --> 12:27.704
which would have given you time
to vacate the premises and you refused.

12:27.830 --> 12:29.247
- Yes, sir.
- We didn't refuse.

12:29.373 --> 12:31.750
- We tried to save our home.
- We were trying to save it.

12:31.876 --> 12:34.127
This is a very painful time, I know.

12:34.253 --> 12:37.881
It's a difficult thing to carry through on,
for me as well.

12:38.007 --> 12:41.176
But the time has come.
You have to leave your property.

12:41.302 --> 12:43.887
You are trespassing right now.
You are breaking the law.

12:44.013 --> 12:46.639
Sir, this is our home
so we just need a few minutes.

12:46.766 --> 12:49.768
We're going in circles here
so I'll let the sheriffs take care of it.

12:49.894 --> 12:51.436
- Randy?
- All right, sir.

12:51.562 --> 12:55.523
We've got a judge, sir,
and a lawyer who told us we can stay.

12:55.649 --> 12:57.901
- Is this your mum?
- Yeah, this is my mum.

12:58.027 --> 13:01.029
I'm gonna need you and your mum
to step off the property now.

13:01.155 --> 13:05.492
You know what? If you all can
come back tomorrow same time

13:05.618 --> 13:08.495
and if we don't have the papers,
we don't have the proof,

13:08.621 --> 13:10.455
- then we will leave.
- We have a lawyer.

13:10.581 --> 13:13.541
- We got it all figured out.
- Just give us a day.

13:13.667 --> 13:15.835
We can dance together,
but we can't talk together.

13:15.961 --> 13:18.713
- OK. All right, sir, we need a day.
- Do not close the door.

13:18.839 --> 13:21.174
- We need a day.
- Listen, this is what I'm gonna do.

13:21.300 --> 13:23.259
- Do not close the door.
- We need a day.

13:23.385 --> 13:26.387
- This is my home. I can do what I want.
- I will give you two minutes

13:26.514 --> 13:28.473
to pack whatever belongings you need

13:28.599 --> 13:32.185
- Cash, chequebook, medicines.
- No, this is not happening.

13:32.311 --> 13:34.771
- Yeah, this is happening.
- No, this is not happening.

13:34.897 --> 13:37.649
I'm getting my cell phone
so I can get the lawyer on the phone.

13:37.775 --> 13:40.944
- Ma'am? Ma'am?
- Excuse me, sir.

13:41.070 --> 13:43.780
- I'm just walking by, sir.
- I don't know what this is.

13:43.906 --> 13:46.616
We can't let someone out of our sight
once we start an eviction.

13:46.742 --> 13:48.827
- Please don't come into my house.
- Listen to me.

13:48.953 --> 13:51.120
There are two ways
that we can do this.

13:51.247 --> 13:54.290
Right? An easy way which is
you do what you're told when asked.

13:54.416 --> 13:57.252
The other way is
that I take you and your mum to jail.

13:57.378 --> 13:58.878
Do you want
your mum to go to jail?

13:59.004 --> 14:01.673
What I'd like you to do
is take advantage of the two minutes,

14:01.799 --> 14:02.882
gather what you need,

14:03.008 --> 14:05.718
cash, cheque books, medicines,
things that you need...

14:05.845 --> 14:09.013
Excuse me, sir, would you mind
stepping outside of the property?

14:09.139 --> 14:12.475
Listen to me, sir.
Let me put it to you this way.

14:12.601 --> 14:14.644
- Excuse me.
- This isn't your home, son.

14:14.770 --> 14:16.479
(Dennis) Mr Carver?
(Lynn) Excuse me.

14:16.605 --> 14:20.650
- Mr Carver?
- According to Florida statute 801.08

14:20.776 --> 14:24.028
- I have the authority...
- Sir, we have the right to an attorney.

14:24.154 --> 14:26.447
(Lynn) Right? Then why
are you coming into our house?

14:26.574 --> 14:28.867
Somebody forgot to call you,
we don't get a lawyer?

14:28.993 --> 14:30.785
It's better not to get emotional, ma'am.

14:30.911 --> 14:33.913
- You're kicking us out of our house.
- Please, OK? Please!

14:34.039 --> 14:36.124
(Sheriff) Ma'am,
please don't ask questions.

14:36.250 --> 14:38.585
- Please!
- Enough of this. Let's go.

14:38.711 --> 14:40.837
Get what you need to get,
then you need to go.

14:40.963 --> 14:44.465
- Let's go. No more of this.
- (Lyn) Sir, I don't need your help.

14:44.592 --> 14:46.259
OK? I can take a minute.

14:46.385 --> 14:48.761
Do you need to follow a woman
into her bedroom?

14:52.182 --> 14:54.350
I got a full house here.

14:54.476 --> 14:57.729
I'm gonna have to be late
to the next one. I know.

14:57.855 --> 15:01.149
It's just department policy.
Money, chequebook.

15:01.275 --> 15:04.110
- Things like wallets, pictures.
- I'm trying to get pictures!

15:04.236 --> 15:06.112
- Does he have to stand there?
- Yes, sir.

15:06.238 --> 15:09.532
He has to fucking stand there
while she packs up her underwear?

15:09.658 --> 15:10.700
Is that right?

15:10.826 --> 15:13.620
(Lynn) Dennis, please!
(Sheriff) It's policy.

15:21.462 --> 15:24.005
Excuse me, sir. Excuse me.

15:24.131 --> 15:26.507
I got to keep you in my sight, ma'am.
Sorry about that.

15:28.385 --> 15:31.804
Anyway, ma'am, just take
the most important things.

15:40.022 --> 15:41.064
What else, Mum?

15:43.067 --> 15:45.693
Can I ask if it says two minutes
on your clipboard?

15:45.819 --> 15:48.529
(Rick) The two minutes is a courtesy.
Let her take the plant.

15:48.656 --> 15:50.615
- You don't need it.
- The two minutes is what?

15:50.741 --> 15:52.200
- A courtesy.
- (Lynn) Oh, my God!

15:52.326 --> 15:54.035
You're trespassing right now.

15:54.161 --> 15:56.913
I know it's painful to hear it,
but it's the truth.

15:58.290 --> 15:59.749
(Lynn) This is our home.

16:01.502 --> 16:04.504
- Oh, my God.
- Anything else, ma'am?

16:04.630 --> 16:05.922
Oh, my toaster.

16:06.048 --> 16:09.050
My toaster oven
to make toast for my grandson.

16:09.176 --> 16:10.760
Uh-huh. Ma'am.

16:17.184 --> 16:19.978
(Lynn) Dennis! Did you get
your chequebook out of the desk?

16:20.104 --> 16:23.398
- You said the two minutes was up.
- (Dennis) We're getting the bills.

16:23.524 --> 16:25.525
- All right, let's go.
- (Lynn) Dennis?

16:26.860 --> 16:29.404
(Lynn) His basketball, his basketball.

16:29.530 --> 16:31.489
Will you just let her go in
and get the ball?

16:31.615 --> 16:34.033
Right, Jeff, get to it.
Rhonda, get the locks.

16:35.035 --> 16:36.494
(Lynn) Hey, what about the rest?

16:36.620 --> 16:38.579
(Rick) They're gonna
bring everything out.

16:38.706 --> 16:40.081
There's no need to worry.

16:41.542 --> 16:44.419
You mind helping me move all this
to the other side of the sidewalk?

16:44.545 --> 16:46.462
We're moving it, OK?
Just give us a second.

16:48.090 --> 16:50.425
Now, my advice would be
to get a moving truck

16:50.551 --> 16:52.510
cos your neighbours
are gonna have access

16:52.636 --> 16:54.721
to everything you own
by the end of the day.

16:54.847 --> 16:57.181
(Dennis) I got it.
(Lynn) Can you believe this?

16:58.392 --> 17:01.728
They cancelled it and then
they didn't even tell these guys.

17:03.397 --> 17:05.064
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.

17:05.190 --> 17:06.398
Oh, my God.

17:06.525 --> 17:09.902
Oh, my God. Oh, my God.
I can't believe this is happening.

17:17.411 --> 17:18.911
Hey!

17:19.038 --> 17:21.079
- What are you doing?
- Moving stuff.

17:21.205 --> 17:23.499
