38:03.489 --> 38:07.826
So you're not just stealing from me,
you're stealing from the US government.

38:08.953 --> 38:11.997
I'm with Frank Greene now.
What have you got for me?

38:12.123 --> 38:14.207
Remove the lines.

38:22.717 --> 38:25.885
I saw you at the foreclosure court.

38:26.012 --> 38:30.015
Our boys go to the same school.
They were playing with the globe.

38:30.141 --> 38:33.560
- Oh, yeah.
- I had my show-cause hearing.

38:34.603 --> 38:37.230
- What happened with you?
- I lost.

38:38.774 --> 38:41.026
Got evicted,
living in a motel right now.

38:43.195 --> 38:44.654
What are you doing with him?

38:45.865 --> 38:47.574
I got to work, you know.

38:47.700 --> 38:49.242
He offered me a job.

38:50.161 --> 38:52.829
I usually do construction, but...

38:52.955 --> 38:54.998
it's been dry for the last however long.

38:57.376 --> 39:00.045
- You know, this ain't what I do.
- This isn't me either.

39:02.340 --> 39:04.549
I was a manager,
Custom Cabinets and Lighting.

39:05.760 --> 39:08.345
Lost my job two years ago. Two.

39:08.471 --> 39:10.847
I'm not a thief.

39:11.807 --> 39:12.891
I know.

39:13.017 --> 39:15.894
I've been researching
on the internet, public libraries.

39:16.020 --> 39:17.645
I'm gonna save my house.

39:18.564 --> 39:20.023
I hope you do.

39:22.735 --> 39:25.362
Custom Cabinets?
Yeah, I installed your stuff.

39:25.488 --> 39:27.489
- Oh, yeah. A bunch of times.
- Hey, Dad.

39:28.491 --> 39:30.950
- Yes?
- The TV turned off.

39:31.077 --> 39:32.494
OK.

39:32.620 --> 39:34.746
You know my boy?
Connor? Connor Nash?

39:34.872 --> 39:36.081
Yes, sir.

39:36.207 --> 39:37.248
Yeah, thanks.

39:39.168 --> 39:43.380
Looks like the Bank of Greater Santa Fe
filed for final judgment of foreclosure.

39:43.506 --> 39:47.675
My money says the judge has me back
for your eviction in less than 90 days.

39:47.802 --> 39:51.596
I took down the extension cords
and the hose.

39:51.722 --> 39:53.640
I shouldn't have done that.
I apologise.

39:53.766 --> 39:55.892
- It's OK.
- No, I assure you, stealing is not OK.

39:56.018 --> 39:58.812
Mr Nash will be talking
to your neighbours personally.

39:58.938 --> 40:00.397
If we receive any reports

40:00.523 --> 40:03.316
or if we drive by and see you
stealing my water and power again,

40:03.442 --> 40:05.735
the next visit's
from the Sheriff's Department.

40:05.861 --> 40:07.487
Understand me?

40:07.613 --> 40:09.364
- Yes, sir.
- Good day.

40:09.490 --> 40:10.615
Nash, come on.

40:15.079 --> 40:16.329
Don't be soft.

40:17.373 --> 40:19.457
They all got a sob story.

40:19.583 --> 40:22.168
But the law's the law.
That's the side you're on.

40:23.087 --> 40:26.589
You should be smart enough
to know the outcome of this situation.

40:26.715 --> 40:28.091
So toughen up.

40:33.097 --> 40:36.057
(Rick) I'm evicting a hedge-fund manager
out of here in two weeks.

40:36.183 --> 40:37.851
Keep your mouth shut
and your eyes open

40:37.977 --> 40:39.978
and maybe you'll learn something
this time.

40:44.233 --> 40:47.152
I'll take the Moder sconces,
the chandelier,

40:47.278 --> 40:50.738
the Haleakala marble,
Harwood cabinets,

40:50.865 --> 40:52.866
range, Sub-Zero.

40:54.285 --> 40:56.445
- What about the microwave?
- I don't need a microwave.

40:56.495 --> 40:59.330
Three grand and you gotta
be out in two weeks.

40:59.457 --> 41:01.541
- How about five?
- Four.

41:01.667 --> 41:03.293
And Dennis here will get right to it.

41:04.503 --> 41:05.837
Done.

41:08.966 --> 41:11.342
The screws are right on in there.
Pop 'em right out, OK?

41:11.469 --> 41:12.552
Yup.

41:18.267 --> 41:19.309
(Beeping)

41:33.115 --> 41:35.992
Install everything, patch the tiles,
caulk the cabinets.

41:36.118 --> 41:38.453
Connect the gas line
when you bring in the appliances.

41:38.579 --> 41:41.247
- All this in here now?
- I'm selling this home for Fannie Mae.

41:41.373 --> 41:44.167
I can't do that
if it doesn't have a kitchen, can I?

41:44.293 --> 41:45.627
No.

41:45.753 --> 41:48.129
So, who just paid me $33,000

41:48.255 --> 41:52.258
for new cabinets, appliances
and a counter top plus labour?

41:54.011 --> 41:55.512
- Fannie Mae.
- Fannie Mae.

41:55.638 --> 41:58.306
Congratulations.
You just fucked the government.

42:02.144 --> 42:04.187
- Mr Nash?
- Yeah.

42:11.153 --> 42:12.695
If you're interested, let me know.

42:12.821 --> 42:15.156
If not, you can use this
to take your kid to Disney World

42:15.282 --> 42:18.368
and get yourself a job
Migueling Cinderella's castle.

42:42.518 --> 42:44.727
I don't give a shit about the government.

42:44.853 --> 42:47.272
They ain't never done
nothing for me, so...

42:47.398 --> 42:49.816
That's a lot of money
you just gave me.

42:49.942 --> 42:51.734
Feels a bit like trouble.

42:51.860 --> 42:54.279
You done honest work
your whole life building homes.

42:54.405 --> 42:57.532
What did that get you
but me knocking at your door?

42:57.658 --> 43:00.076
Are we stealing? Is this stealing?

43:00.202 --> 43:03.413
Well, in 2006 you borrowed $85,000
against your home

43:03.539 --> 43:05.290
and never paid it back, Nash.

43:05.416 --> 43:08.793
- You telling me that's not stealing?
- What? Are you serious?

43:08.919 --> 43:10.878
That's not stealing,
that's me taking a loan.

43:11.005 --> 43:13.298
That's me working my arse off
to pay back that loan.

43:13.424 --> 43:15.174
I wanted to pay it back.
I didn't steal.

43:15.301 --> 43:18.928
That's not how the banks see it
or the taxpayers paying for the bail-out.

43:19.054 --> 43:20.555
You think I bought a Porsche? No.

43:20.681 --> 43:24.309
I invested every cent I borrowed
into construction equipment

43:24.435 --> 43:28.104
so that I could pay back that loan
and put a roof over my family's head,

43:28.230 --> 43:29.939
put food in my kid's mouth.

43:31.025 --> 43:33.318
The economy crashed.
I can't predict the weather.

43:33.444 --> 43:35.528
I can.

43:35.654 --> 43:38.156
I'm a Doppler fucking radar.

43:38.282 --> 43:41.284
You took something you didn't give back.
The bank screwed you over.

43:41.410 --> 43:44.537
Take your pick.
Either way you lost.

43:44.663 --> 43:47.373
But I made more money
during the crash than before it.

43:47.499 --> 43:51.210
You can too, you just gotta stop
lying to yourself and ask,

43:51.337 --> 43:54.589
what did you do wrong
that your family lives in a motel?

44:04.266 --> 44:05.308
I'm gonna do it.

44:06.685 --> 44:08.728
Whatever you want me to do,
I'll do it, but...

44:10.481 --> 44:12.982
I need you to do me a favour,
help me get my family home back.

44:13.108 --> 44:15.693
I want you to take this
as my first payment.

44:15.819 --> 44:17.570
Don't get emotional about real estate.

44:17.696 --> 44:19.697
It's too late for that.
That's my family home.

44:19.823 --> 44:22.492
That's my boy's school,
so please just take this.

44:22.618 --> 44:24.994
This ain't gonna cut it.
Put that under your mattress.

44:25.120 --> 44:28.539
Don't put it in the bank.
You're just giving them more money.

44:28.666 --> 44:31.042
When you get enough
I'll tell you what to do with it.

44:31.168 --> 44:33.461
Now, do you want to double
what you just made or not?

44:36.840 --> 44:38.841
(Car horn honks)

44:38.967 --> 44:41.636
It's about fucking time, playboy.

44:44.431 --> 44:45.473
Damn.

44:47.059 --> 44:49.143
Always late, papa.
You always late, man.

44:49.728 --> 44:51.187
Yeah.

44:51.313 --> 44:53.231
That's the jackpot.

44:55.067 --> 44:57.694
- So who's this Rick Carver dude?
- That's my boss.

44:57.820 --> 44:59.612
For the time being.

44:59.738 --> 45:01.989
- What's that like?
- Oh, it's great. He's...

45:02.116 --> 45:03.991
Nah, he's a fucking arsehole.

45:04.118 --> 45:06.869
One, two, three.
Straight on.

45:08.831 --> 45:10.832
- What are you doing?
- Got to take a picture.

45:10.958 --> 45:14.043
To prove to the bank this shit's missing
so they pay us to put it back in.

45:14.169 --> 45:17.255
We're stealing it
to then bring it back?

45:17.381 --> 45:18.840
- You wanna get paid?
- Hell, yeah.

45:18.966 --> 45:20.007
I got to take a picture.

45:24.263 --> 45:26.305
- Yeah?
- Mr Tanner, my name is Dennis Nash.

45:26.432 --> 45:29.016
I'm here representing
Rick Carver Realty.

45:29.143 --> 45:31.269
Um, I'm here to, er...

45:31.395 --> 45:33.771
I understand your house
has been foreclosed on.

45:33.897 --> 45:37.400
The house still belongs to us
and we intend to keep it that way.

45:37.526 --> 45:39.819
I hope that works out.
God forbid it doesn't.

45:39.945 --> 45:42.530
If you got a second
I wanna tell you about cash for keys,

45:42.656 --> 45:44.615
here on the form.

45:44.742 --> 45:46.492
What do you mean,
cash for keys?

45:46.618 --> 45:49.245
(Dennis) If you leave your house
in a broom-swept condition

45:49.371 --> 45:50.621
prior to your eviction date,

45:50.748 --> 45:52.874
banks can give you 3500 bucks
cash in your pocket.

45:53.000 --> 45:56.836
We're not interested in anything.
Take your papers.

45:56.962 --> 46:01.007
We'll contact our attorney
and they'll get with you.

46:15.022 --> 46:16.063
What you doing, son?

46:16.190 --> 46:18.399
Who'll buy a home with a pool
if the pool don't work?

46:18.525 --> 46:20.902
- What do y'all think y'all doing?
- Doing some repairs.

46:21.028 --> 46:23.738
I know this house has been empty
for two or three months.

46:23.864 --> 46:26.574
You know Rick Carver Realty?
You see that sign on the lawn?

46:26.700 --> 46:28.451
- Yes, I did.
- That's who we work for.

46:28.577 --> 46:30.286
I hope you have a good day.

46:30.412 --> 46:32.371
- Is she your type?
- Yeah, yeah, yeah!

46:32.498 --> 46:34.373
It ain't a lot,
but it's gonna pay for U-Haul,

46:34.500 --> 46:36.626
storage, a down payment
on an apartment.

46:36.752 --> 46:39.170
I have no idea what's going on.

46:39.296 --> 46:43.925
Because my mum and dad
from Vietnam is coming

46:44.051 --> 46:45.760
and the house can't be foreclosured.

46:46.929 --> 46:48.846
Have you been putting notices
on my window?

46:48.972 --> 46:52.225
- No, that's the Sheriff's Department.
- Well, that's trespassing.

46:52.351 --> 46:55.353
I can't control what the department does,
but I can give you this form.

46:55.479 --> 46:57.647
I don't want your papers.
Don't hand me no papers.

46:57.773 --> 47:00.900
I don't want your papers or notices.
I want you to get the hell out of here.

47:08.742 --> 47:11.869
I've been owning this house
for seven years already.

47:11.995 --> 47:13.955
I met my wife right here.

47:14.081 --> 47:17.875
We're about to have a baby here.
I just made an addition in the back.

47:18.001 --> 47:20.795
I wanna save the house.
I wanna keep it.

47:20.921 --> 47:24.173
- Who are you?
- I work for a real estate company.

47:24.758 --> 47:28.928
This is a KYO form. Basically,
it means knowing your options.

47:29.054 --> 47:32.056
- My options?
- I'm putting it all on Facebook.

47:32.182 --> 47:34.767
- Kayla, put it away.
- We don't know who this man is.

47:34.893 --> 47:37.228
Kayla, go inside.

47:42.860 --> 47:43.985
I'm sorry, ma'am.

47:44.111 --> 47:46.279
I'm gonna have to take care of my kid.

47:46.405 --> 47:48.948
I advise you to call
that number at the bo...

47:49.074 --> 47:51.784
- If you wanna just take a look.
- I'm not looking at anything.

47:51.910 --> 47:53.828
You could just take it
and not look at it.

47:53.954 --> 47:55.621
Hold on a second.

47:57.249 --> 48:00.835
I think I've made myself clear to you.
I don't wanna see you again.

48:25.444 --> 48:28.613
Both Victor and Andy.
Neither one of them showed up.

48:28.739 --> 48:30.197
- Hey.
- Hey.

48:31.158 --> 48:33.200
I can't even give Connor his vitamins.

48:33.327 --> 48:35.828
I have one little kid Flintstone vitamin.

48:35.954 --> 48:37.121
(Day) They're good.

48:37.247 --> 48:39.999
- What do you got in there?
- What do you have in there?

48:41.919 --> 48:43.127
- A steak.
- What?

48:43.253 --> 48:45.796
That's Hamburger Helper
if I ever heard of anything.

48:45.923 --> 48:48.174
What does that look like to you?

48:48.300 --> 48:50.468
That looks like dinner for Day and I.

48:50.594 --> 48:52.178
Day, you come on and join us.

48:52.304 --> 48:54.889
You put that under your T-shirt.

48:55.015 --> 48:56.724
No, I'm not kidding.

48:56.850 --> 48:59.268
(Day and Lynn chatting)

49:01.396 --> 49:03.981
Oh, that was in.
Come on, Dad!

49:06.193 --> 49:07.860
Watch the lamp!

49:23.627 --> 49:28.130
One, two, three, four, five,
six, seven, eight ACs.

49:29.466 --> 49:30.883
And five pool pumps.

49:31.009 --> 49:33.970
- A good addition.
- I figured why not.

49:34.096 --> 49:37.390
Better count on seven.
I dropped that one. It's beyond repair.

49:37.516 --> 49:40.226
- Sell it for scrap metal.
- I already priced it out. 100 bucks.

49:40.352 --> 49:42.812
Good. Invoice Rick Carver Realty

49:42.938 --> 49:46.107
24K for the ACs
and 3200 for the pumps.

49:46.233 --> 49:48.859
The bank will reimburse me
to the same amount.

49:48.986 --> 49:51.904
Your cut is 25%, about 6700.

49:53.532 --> 49:56.033
- 6700?
- That's right.

49:57.953 --> 49:59.537
- Hey, Rick.
- What?

50:00.747 --> 50:02.206
You still got that Ruger?

50:04.001 --> 50:06.627
Excuse me? What did you say?

50:06.753 --> 50:09.463
Are you saying you want the gun?
Did I understand you?

50:17.014 --> 50:19.932
I ran the background check already.
You're clear to carry it.

50:24.104 --> 50:26.981
Who pays the most out
in cash for keys?

50:27.107 --> 50:29.233
Fannie and Freddie, then BoA.

50:29.359 --> 50:31.944
I want you to go to every one
of their foreclosed properties

50:32.070 --> 50:33.612
and find any that are unoccupied.

50:33.739 --> 50:35.906
(Rick) No homeowner, no tenant.
You got it?

50:36.033 --> 50:37.742
Yo, Terry, let's go.

50:37.868 --> 50:40.578
- Motherfucker didn't pay again.
- We got some money for you.

50:42.122 --> 50:45.041
Send 'em back, Luis.
Send 'em back, brother.

50:45.167 --> 50:48.002
- Dennis, where are we going?
- Be patient. Don't ask questions.

50:48.128 --> 50:50.755
- You don't trust me?
- You hired me, so I got no choice.

50:53.759 --> 50:55.176
Go, Terry.

51:02.476 --> 51:05.144
- Tell him to hurry up.
- Yo, T, let's go, baby.

51:05.270 --> 51:08.147
There's nobody here.
11286. There's nobody here.

51:08.273 --> 51:09.857
All right, bub. Jump in.

51:12.819 --> 51:14.570
(Dennis) How we doing, Javi?

51:18.241 --> 51:21.410
267 Lakewood.
Empty as a motherfucker.

51:21.536 --> 51:24.371
Right, turn to the back page.
I need y'all to sign these leases.

51:24.498 --> 51:29.251
The banks need to think you guys
are tenants in all these properties,

51:29.377 --> 51:32.088
so that I can negotiate
cash-for-keys deals with all y'all.

51:32.214 --> 51:35.508
- How much they paying?
- You can count on a $2500 cheque

51:35.634 --> 51:38.135
from the government
and the motherfucking banks.

51:38.261 --> 51:39.678
(Javier) 2500?

51:39.805 --> 51:43.057
They been fucking me for so long, man.
Shit, I'll take it back, brother.

51:43.183 --> 51:45.226
Somebody getting pregnant
tonight, baby.

51:47.479 --> 51:49.897
Who we fucking, man?
The government or the banks?

52:03.995 --> 52:08.165
Ah, Jim. See you for lunch
Wednesday, OK?

52:08.291 --> 52:09.834
You think Freeman
is the way to go?

52:09.960 --> 52:12.461
He's Fannie's number one attorney
three years running.

52:12.587 --> 52:14.713
He can connect us to bulk buyers.

52:14.840 --> 52:17.758
I'm not talking millions of dollars,
I'm talking billions.

52:20.011 --> 52:21.554
All right, so this is Dennis Nash.

52:21.680 --> 52:24.014
- County Commissioner Arthur Link.
- Pleasure.

52:24.141 --> 52:26.058
Your property at 2102 West Jefferson,

52:26.184 --> 52:28.561
I'll have Dennis make sure
the gutters are redone.

52:28.687 --> 52:30.396
- What happened to Bill?
- Killed him.

52:30.522 --> 52:32.731
This is my new guy.
I think he's gonna last.

52:32.858 --> 52:36.569
I'll get us a meeting with Freeman.
And stick with this guy, you'll go far.

52:36.695 --> 52:38.737
(Rick) Thanks for the recommendation.

52:38.864 --> 52:40.072
See you, Arthur.

52:43.910 --> 52:45.202
(Rick) What do you got for me?

52:45.328 --> 52:48.414
Successfully negotiated
six cash-for-keys with six tenants.

52:48.540 --> 52:53.335
Good. So, Nash, how much
did you tell your buddies per home?

52:53.461 --> 52:56.088
- 3500 or less?
- Yeah, 3500.

52:57.591 --> 52:59.383
Oh, you told them the full amount?

53:01.845 --> 53:03.429
I told 'em what I told 'em.

53:04.472 --> 53:05.890
What do you care?

53:10.228 --> 53:11.854
Yeah.

53:19.988 --> 53:22.656
Hey, baby. Look at that smile.
You're gorgeous.

53:25.118 --> 53:26.619
Don't you have class today?

53:26.745 --> 53:29.163
Er, they're all online,
plus I finished that website.

53:29.289 --> 53:30.956
Congratulations.

53:36.671 --> 53:37.713
She's my sweetheart.

53:37.839 --> 53:40.174
Studies graphic design.
I had her do my business card.

53:43.386 --> 53:45.429
- This your place?
- No, just keeping it warm.

53:45.555 --> 53:48.641
Why don't you scan those leases
and email them to Fannie and BoA.

53:53.939 --> 53:55.981
So, Nash, why aren't you married?

53:58.193 --> 53:59.902
I don't really got time for it.

54:00.028 --> 54:02.655
I don't trust a man who's not married.
Nobody does.

54:02.781 --> 54:04.782
Wanna tell me
what happened to Connor's mum?

54:07.244 --> 54:09.119
I don't think so, no.

54:10.789 --> 54:12.623
Prom night fiasco?

54:15.085 --> 54:17.378
Close, pretty close.

54:17.504 --> 54:21.257
The cheque for the AC
and pool pumps came in.

54:21.383 --> 54:23.300
It's a lot higher
than what I expected.

54:23.426 --> 54:24.468
7200.

54:25.595 --> 54:27.054
You wanna keep that?

54:27.180 --> 54:29.682
I'll give you the three grand
I already made.

54:29.808 --> 54:32.810
And whatever my share is
from these leases.

54:36.523 --> 54:38.607
Cos I want my home back.

54:40.026 --> 54:42.820
The BPO on your home
came in at 170K.

54:44.322 --> 54:46.031
I'll buy it

54:46.157 --> 54:48.242
and then you'll owe me 155

54:48.368 --> 54:52.913
at 12% amortised over a 30-year period
with a two-year balloon.

54:55.333 --> 54:57.960
That's a shitty rate, Rick.

54:58.086 --> 54:59.795
No bank's gonna loan you that money.

54:59.921 --> 55:01.338
If you don't pay, I'm on the hook.

55:01.464 --> 55:03.507
I don't want that property.
It has no future.

55:03.633 --> 55:06.010
- Yeah, but that's my family home.
- It's a home.

55:06.136 --> 55:08.637
But if you want it, it's yours.

55:08.763 --> 55:12.391
It'll take eight to 12 weeks
for the bank to list it on the MLS.

55:12.517 --> 55:14.852
You can do repairs,
but you can't move in till then.

55:16.021 --> 55:17.813
Can we figure out
some kind of contract?

55:17.939 --> 55:20.816
Yeah, I'll have the office
draw up a contract for deed.

55:24.571 --> 55:26.822
Is it mine again?

55:26.948 --> 55:28.657
Yeah, it's yours.

55:28.783 --> 55:29.950
OK, thank you.

55:31.244 --> 55:32.286
Seriously, thank you.

55:32.412 --> 55:34.496
- Rick, thank you.
- All right.

55:36.124 --> 55:37.166
No tears.

55:40.253 --> 55:41.295
Drink?

55:44.841 --> 55:46.175
No, I'm good, I'm good.

55:46.301 --> 55:47.760
High on life.

55:47.886 --> 55:49.928
Well, you might wanna reconsider.

55:50.055 --> 55:52.181
We got one more stop.

55:52.307 --> 55:54.350
224 Lake View Court.

55:55.810 --> 55:59.313
Is that Mr Tanner? I offered him
a cash-for-keys from the bank.

55:59.439 --> 56:01.899
Guess what? He never called.
And his eviction's today.

56:02.025 --> 56:03.692
You can pop your cherry
